de.feig.FEDM.Core

Class ITagGroup

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.feig.FEDM.Core.ITagGroup

  • public class ITagGroup
extends java.lang.Object
    Internal class providing Transponder specific Reader commands, when the Reader is working in Host-Mode.
    Description:
    This class realizes the nested interface with transponder specific methods like Inventory and Select for the Reader class ReaderModule.
    The communication with Transponders is realized with TagHandler classes, which will be served with methods of this class.
    Methods of this class can be called with the ReaderModule.ITag member of ReaderModule.

    The concept of TagHandler classes provides an efficient programming interface with different transponder types. It is based on the automatic identification of the type of the transponder after a successful inventory. With ISO 15693 compliant transponders the manufacturer ID and the chipID, which are part of the serial number, are evaluated. With ISO 14443 compliant transponders the type of the TagHandler can be determined after a mandatory Select command based on the returned Card-Info or, in case of the explicit selection of a transponder driver with the Select comand, the transponder driver selects the type of the TagHandler.
    All TagHandler classes are derived from the base class TH_Base. Furthermore, the relationship between the different transponder types is maped to derivations between TagHandler classes.
    TagHandler classes are created, managed and deleted internally. After each call of inventory(boolean, byte, byte), the Reader class checks the present state of each TagHandler and removes the handler if the dedicated transponder is out of field. Thus, the life cycle of a TagHandler is normally one inventory cycle.

      • inventory

        public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,TH_Base> inventory(boolean all,
                                                             byte mode,
                                                             byte antennas)
                                                      throws FeException
        Method executes synchronous Inventory command (for all IDENTIFICATION Readers).
        Parameters:
        all - when true, Inventory is repeated as long as the Reader respond MORE status.
        mode - MODE byte to adjust the Inventory. See Reader's System Manual for additional information.
        antennas - Antenna Flag field to select specific antenna(s). Only available for Readers with internal Multiplexer.
        Returns:
        List with all detected Transponder objects (TagHandler classes) or an empty list, if anything goes wrong
        Throws:
        FeException - exception with error code (<0)

        Description:
        Call of an Inventory and returning of all found tags in a TagList of type TagHandler base class TH_Base.
        If anything goes wrong, the returned list is empty and the reason can be evaluated with the methods ReaderModule.getLastError() and ReaderModule.getLastStatus().
        If applicable, the returned Transponder information is analyzed and the dedicated TagHandler class is created. In all other cases, the TagHandler base class is created.

        Example:
        The following example demonstrates the principle work with inventory, how to identify the returned TagHandler types and how to work with the Transponder objects.
         

  NOTE: reader is an object of type de.feig.FEDM.Core.ReaderModule
 
  import de.feig.FEDM.Core.*;
  import de.feig.FEDM.Core.TagHandler.*;
 
   HashMap<String, TH_Base> tagList = new HashMap<String, TH_Base>();
  TH_Base th = null;
  int tagDriver = 0;

  try
  {
      // inventory call with options: for all Tags, standard mode, standard Antenna or actual selected Antenna
      tagList = reader.ITag.inventory(true, (byte)0, (byte)1);
 
      // iteration loop over all detected Transponders
       for ( Map.Entry<String, TH_Base> e : tagList.entrySet() )
      {
          th = e.getValue();// TagHandler from HashMap
          switch(th.getTagHandlerType()
          {
          // is selected Transponder of standard ISO 15693?
          case TH_Base.TH_ISO15693)
              TH_ISO15693 thIso = (TH_ISO15693)th;
              System.out.println(thIso.getManufacturerName());
              
          // is selected Transponder of standard ISO 14443-4?
          case TH_Base.TH_ISO14443_4)
              // select Transponder:
              th = reader.ITag.select(th, tagDriver);
              TH_ISO14443_4 thIso = (TH_ISO14443_4)th;
              System.out.println(thIso.getManufacturerName());
              
          case TH_Base.TH_EPC_Class1_Gen2)
              TH_EPC_Class1_Gen2 thGen2 = (TH_EPC_Class1_Gen2)th;
              // write new EPC to Transponder (withoutPassword)
              thGen2.writeEPC("0102030405060708090A0B0C", "");
          }
      }
  }
  catch()
  {
      if(reader.getLastError() < 0)
      {
          // we have an internal error
          System.out.println(ErrorCode.getErrorText(reader.getLastError()));
      }
      else
      {
          if(reader.getLastStatus() > 0)
          {
              // we have a feedback from the Reader
              System.out.println(reader.getStatusText(reader.getLastStatus()));
          }
      }
  }

      • select

        public TH_Base select(TH_Base tagHandler,
                      int tagDriver)
               throws FeException
        Method for executing a synchronous Select command (for all IDENTIFICATION Readers, if supported by the applied standard)
        Parameters:
        tagHandler - A TagHandler object from the TagHandler-List, created by inventory(boolean, byte, byte).
        tagDriver - Optional transponder driver to be used for the Select comnand
        Returns:
        TagHandler object in selected state (can be based on a new TagHandler class) or null in error cases (e.g. loss of transponder)
        Throws:
        FeException - exception with error code (<0)

        Description:
        A [0xB0][0x25] Select command is executed. The command is controlled by an optional tagDriver.
        The parameter tagDriver is explained in detail in the Reader's system manual.

        Example:
        See the following example how to identify the returned TagHandler type and how to work with the Transponder object.
         

  NOTE: reader is an object of type de.feig.FEDM.Core.ReaderModule
 
  import de.feig.FEDM.Core.*;
  import de.feig.FEDM.Core.TagHandler.*;
 
  TH_Base th = reader.ITag.getTagHandler("0123456789ABCDEF");
  TH_Base thSel = null;
  int tagDriver = 0;
 
  // select Transponder:
  thSel = reader.ITag.select(th, tagDriver);
  if( thSel != null )
  {
      System.out.println(thSel.getManufacturerName());
  }
